  "text": "HTTP/1.1 to HTTP/2 header translation and normalization in Envoy occurs across multiple codec implementations and utility modules in the envoyproxy/envoy repository:\n\n## Header Case Normalization (Lowercase)\n\nIn `source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc` (line 568), the HTTP/1 codec's `ConnectionImpl::completeCurrentHeader()` method normalizes header names to lowercase using: `current_header_field_.inlineTransform([](char c) { return absl::ascii_tolower(c); });`. This is a critical transformation that happens as HTTP/1.1 headers are parsed.\n\nFor HTTP/2, the `source/common/http/http2/codec_impl.cc` contains the `StaticHeaderNameLookup` class (lines 42-110) which manages well-known HTTP/2 pseudo-headers and common headers with lowercase mapping. The HTTP/2 visitor callback `ConnectionImpl::Http2Visitor::OnHeaderForStream()` (line 1910) uses this lookup to reference pre-computed lowercase strings for common headers like `:method`, `:path`, `:scheme`, `:authority`, `:status`, etc.\n\n## Pseudo-Header Injection\n\nThe pseudo-header transformation happens in the HTTP/2 codec at multiple points:\n1. In `source/common/http/http2/codec_impl.cc`, the `StaticHeaderNameLookup` explicitly maps HTTP/2 pseudo-headers (lines 48-54):\n   - `:authority` maps to `headers.Host`\n   - `:method` maps to `headers.Method`\n   - `:path` maps to `headers.Path`\n   - `:scheme` maps to `headers.Scheme`\n   - `:status` maps to `headers.Status`\n   - `:protocol` maps to `headers.Protocol`\n\n2. In HTTP/1 codec's `ServerConnectionImpl::handlePath()` (source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc, line 1115), the `:path` pseudo-header is set from the parsed HTTP/1 request line using `headers.setPath()`.\n\n3. In `ServerConnectionImpl::onHeadersCompleteBase()` (source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc, line 1201), the `:method` is injected via `headers.setMethod(parser_->methodName())`.\n\n## Upgrade Header Handling\n\nUpgrade header transformation is handled in `source/common/http/utility.cc`:\n- `Utility::transformUpgradeRequestFromH2toH1()` (line 1229) converts HTTP/2 upgrade requests to HTTP/1 format\n- `Utility::transformUpgradeResponseFromH2toH1()` (line 1242) converts HTTP/2 upgrade responses to HTTP/1 format\n- `Utility::removeConnectionUpgrade()` (line 714) removes upgrade-related headers from the Connection header\n\nIn `source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc` (lines 863-880), the codec explicitly handles upgrade headers by removing unsupported `h2c` (HTTP/2 Cleartext) upgrade headers and managing the Connection header.\n\n## HTTP/1 to HTTP/2 Bridge Filter\n\nThe `source/extensions/filters/http/grpc_http1_bridge/http1_bridge_filter.cc` provides gRPC-specific HTTP/1 to HTTP/2 translation. The filter detects HTTP/1 gRPC requests (line 47) and bridges them to HTTP/2 by:\n1. Setting the content-type to gRPC format (line 38)\n2. Handling protobuf upgrades (lines 36-39)\n3. Managing query parameter removal (lines 25-31)\n\n## QUIC/HTTP/3 Header Translation\n\nIn `source/common/quic/envoy_quic_utils.h` and `.cc`, header conversion utilities handle both directions:\n- `quicHeadersToEnvoyHeaders()` (template function, lines 78-117) converts QUIC headers to Envoy HeaderMap with lowercase normalization\n- `http2HeaderBlockToEnvoyTrailers()` (lines 121-161) converts HTTP/2 header blocks to Envoy trailers\n- `envoyHeadersToHttp2HeaderBlock()` (source/common/quic/envoy_quic_utils.cc, line 111) converts Envoy headers back to HTTP/2 format\n\n## Header Validator Integration\n\nHeader validation for HTTP/1 and HTTP/2 occurs in:\n- `source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/http1_header_validator.cc` - validates HTTP/1 request headers before translation\n- `source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/http2_header_validator.cc` - validates HTTP/2 pseudo-headers and headers after reception\n\nThese validators ensure compliance with RFC 7540 (HTTP/2) and RFC 7230/7231 (HTTP/1.1) before headers are passed to filters and upstream.\n\n## Connection Manager Utilities\n\nThe `source/common/http/conn_manager_utility.cc` provides utilities for header manipulation:\n- `sanitizeConnectionHeader()` removes nominated pseudo-headers from the Connection header\n- `cleanInternalHeaders()` strips internal Envoy headers\n- `isUpgrade()` detects upgrade requests\n- `mutateRequestHeaders()` applies XFF and other header transformations\n\nAll these components work together to ensure HTTP/1.1 requests are properly normalized (headers to lowercase), pseudo-headers are injected (`:method`, `:path`, `:scheme`, `:authority`), and upgrade headers are correctly handled when translating between HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 protocols."
}

